VTS Diarization Sidecar — Third-Party Attribution
==================================================

This container bundles the pyannote speaker-diarization pipeline and its model
weights. Attribution is provided here per the terms of the weights' license.

pyannote.audio
--------------
Software: pyannote.audio (https://github.com/pyannote/pyannote-audio)
License:  MIT

Model weights: speaker-diarization-community-1
--------------------------------------------------
Source:   https://huggingface.co/pyannote-community/speaker-diarization-community-1
License:  CC-BY-4.0 (Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International)
          https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

The following weight artifacts are vendored into this image at build time
(fetch_models.py, verified by pinned sha256) and used at runtime offline:

  - config.yaml                     (pipeline wiring)
  - segmentation/pytorch_model.bin  (speaker segmentation)
  - embedding/pytorch_model.bin     (speaker embedding, WeSpeaker ResNet, 256-dim)
  - plda/plda.npz                   (VBx clustering parameters)
  - plda/xvec_transform.npz         (VBx clustering parameters)

CC-BY-4.0 requires attribution to the original authors. The pyannote authors
and the speaker-diarization-community-1 model are credited above. No changes
were made to the weights; they are redistributed unmodified.

If you cite this work academically, cite the pyannote.audio papers as listed on
the pyannote.audio repository.
